<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-29T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-29T11:00:00-05:00" n="725" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d725">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3831/2a suppl: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Belden</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-29T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">March 29,
                                            1920—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>32. Department’s March 9, 3 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Has Haitian Government issued <hi rend="italic">arrêté</hi> carrying
                                out provisions of the Contract of the Retrait? Memoranda of Minister
                                of Finance on this subject have been considered by Financial
                                Advisor. Department’s March 9, 3 p.m. is answer thereto.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>